#Business Process Model and Notation
flowchart of business process

#elements
event: circle
- start: catch trigger
- intermediate: catch or throw
- end: throw result
activity: rectangle, work
- task
- subprocess
- event subprocess
gateway: diamond, path merge/fork
- exclusive: only one alternative
- inclusive: one or more alternatives
- parallel
- event
sequence flow: arrow, path connection
- conditional
- default
swim line: organization
- pool
- lane

#event
conditional
timer: scheduler
message: individual message
signal: broadcast message
escalation: message within process
error: handle problem
compensation: revert work
termination: end everything
link: divide visually
